title: Easy: FizzBuzz
description:
Write a function `fizzbuzz` that takes an integer `n` as input and prints the numbers from 1 to `n`. For multiples of 3, print "Fizz" instead of the number. For multiples of 5, print "Buzz" instead of the number. For numbers which are multiples of both 3 and 5, print "FizzBuzz" instead of the number.
#### Function Signature
```python
def fizzbuzz(n: int) -> None:
```
#### Input
- `n` (int): An integer representing the upper limit of the sequence.
#### Output
- Prints numbers from 1 to `n`, replacing multiples of 3 with "Fizz", multiples of 5 with "Buzz", and multiples of both 3 and 5 with "FizzBuzz".
